That's a good point. I would really like to make it so that one can build a plugin off a conda installation (it's on one of my todo lists). We used to install all the libraries to `$PREFIX/lib`, but I stopped doing that because they weren't doing anything useful. If the mixed gnu-make (of plugins) and cmake and all the compiler/linker flags that must be in sync could be made to work with plugins, we can definitely make appropriate changes to install.

